      "comment": "PAW XANTIPPE (7) is worth forgiving for her last effort when fifth (30.76) at The Meadows over 525m. Form at the trip sound including nine wins. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. ZIPPING COLUMBUS (1) filled the minor placings again last time when second (30.35) at The Meadows, making it three straight minors on end. Will go close here with a clear run. CRACKERJACK RALF (6) was unfavoured last start but led all the way to score by 2 lengths (27.56) at Bendigo in a Group Listed over 500m. Hard to fault his form and he makes plenty of appeal. DISTINCTION (3) has a solid strike rate at this distance.",
